---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import TerminalQuote from '../components/TerminalQuote.astro';

const nowText =
	"Now: Exploring full-stack development, diving deeper into front-end frameworks, back-end systems, and database technologies, while sharing practical guides and insights on technology and life."
const backgroundText =
	"With a foundation in energy engineering and a passion for technology, I've transitioned into full-stack development, combining analytical thinking with creative problem-solving."
const journeyText =
	"My technical journey began with curiosity about how systems work, leading me to explore various technologies and build practical solutions."
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Zero02, a full-stack developer and tech enthusiast sharing knowledge, experiences, and practical insights across various technology domains."
	pubDate={new Date('Mar 13 2026')}
	heroImage="/image/about/info.webm"
	profileImage="/image/Zero02.jpg"
>
	<p>
		I am Zero02 (零), a passionate full-stack developer and tech enthusiast from China. I believe in practical engineering, clear reasoning, and building systems that can be explained and reproduced. 
		This blog is my long-term notebook for sharing knowledge, experiments, tools, and technical decisions across various technology domains.
	</p>

	<h2>Background</h2>
	<p>
		{backgroundText} I bring a unique perspective to software development, combining the analytical mindset from engineering with the creativity of modern web technologies. 
		My diverse background allows me to approach problems from multiple angles and find innovative solutions.
	</p>

	<h2>Technical Journey</h2>
	<p>
		{journeyText} From learning the basics of programming to building complex web applications, I've always been driven by the desire to create useful tools and share knowledge with others. 
		My approach to learning is hands-on—building projects and experimenting with new technologies to gain practical experience.
	</p>

	<h2>Technical Expertise</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Front-end Development:</strong>
			<ul>
				<li>HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)</li>
				<li>Frameworks: React, Vue, Next.js</li>
				<li>Styling: Tailwind CSS, Sass, Bootstrap, Element Plus & Ant Design</li>
				<li>Tools: Webpack, Vite, npm, pnpm</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Back-end Development:</strong>
			<ul>
				<li>Languages: Java, Node.js</li>
				<li>Frameworks: Spring, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Egg.js</li>
				<li>Deployment: Docker, Linux, CI/CD practices</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Database Technologies:</strong>
			<ul>
				<li>Relational: MySQL, PostgreSQL</li>
				<li>NoSQL: MongoDB, Redis</li>
				<li>Search: Elasticsearch</li>
				<li>ORM: MyBatis-Plus, Hibernate</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>AI & Creative Technologies:</strong>
			<ul>
				<li>Stable Diffusion</li>
				<li>LLM-assisted tooling</li>
				<li>Creative coding</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Content Philosophy</h2>
	<p>
		I create content that is practical, actionable, and focused on real-world applications. Whether it's a step-by-step guide to building a personal blog, a deep dive into a specific technology, or insights on career development, 
		my goal is to provide value that helps others learn and grow in their technical journey. 
		I believe in clear explanations, practical examples, and sharing both successes and challenges to create a comprehensive learning experience.
	</p>

	<h2>Notable Projects</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Personal Blog Platform:</strong> Built with Astro, Tailwind CSS, and Markdown for content management</li>
		<li><strong>GoFile Download Tool:</strong> A utility for batch downloading files from GoFile</li>
		<li><strong>Tablet Second Monitor Setup:</strong> Created a guide for using Sunshine to turn a tablet into a second monitor</li>
		<li><strong>Various Full-Stack Applications:</strong> Built with modern frameworks and best practices</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Learning Approach</h2>
	<p>
		My learning philosophy is centered around <strong>project-based learning</strong> and <strong>continuous improvement</strong>. I believe the best way to learn is by doing, so I'm constantly working on new projects that challenge me to acquire new skills. 
		I also value the importance of sharing knowledge, as teaching others helps reinforce my own understanding.
	</p>

	<h2>Now</h2>
	<TerminalQuote text={nowText} once={true} fixedHeight={false} />

	<h2>Featured Content</h2>
	<p>
		Some of my most popular guides include:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><a href="/blog/how-to-build-a-personal-blog/" target="_self">How to Build a Personal Blog</a></li>
		<li><a href="/blog/how-to-get-started-with-programming/" target="_self">How to Get Started with Programming</a></li>
		<li><a href="/blog/how-i-turned-my-tablet-into-a-second-monitor-with-sunshine/" target="_self">How I Turned My Tablet into a Second Monitor</a></li>
		<li><a href="/blog/gofile-download-tool-guide/" target="_self">GoFile Download Tool Guide</a></li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Personal Interests</h2>
	<p>
		Beyond technology, I enjoy exploring various interests that complement my technical work:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Engineering:</strong> Continuing to follow developments in energy and materials science</li>
		<li><strong>Creativity:</strong> Experimenting with digital art and creative coding</li>
		<li><strong>Learning:</strong> Exploring new technologies and staying updated with industry trends</li>
		<li><strong>Productivity:</strong> Optimizing workflows and tools for efficient development</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Contact</h2>
	<p>
		The most reliable way to reach me is by email:
		<code>zero201913@outlook.com</code>
		or
		<code>crimson201913@gmail.com</code>.
		You can also find me via GitHub and Bilibili from the site navigation.
	</p>

	<h2>Let's Connect</h2>
	<p>
		I'm always open to connecting with fellow developers, collaborating on projects, or discussing new ideas. 
		Feel free to reach out if you have any questions, suggestions, or just want to say hello!
	</p>
</Layout>
